{
  "texts": [
    "This leads to a conundrum: if taken at face value, it could imply that GPT-4 possesses sufficient competence to function as a medical physicist, which appears highly unlikely.",
    "Thus, the mechanics community might need to reconsider their certificate procedures, as the need for humans to extensively learn such potentially superficial knowledge might decrease with the ongoing evolution of LLMs.",
    "In this context, LLMs could serve as a benchmark for superficiality in knowledge assessment.",
    "Emphasizing knowledge areas that LLMs have not mastered might become increasingly important.",
    "Applying large language models in mechanical engineeringThe incorporation of large language models emerges as a groundbreaking asset in the domains of mechanical engineering education and scientific research."
  ]
}